<br>
Now lets take a look at this from another angle.  The &quot;What this class is designed to do&quot; angle.  Clerics = Heal and buffs,  Wizards = direct damage, ports,  Necro = dots and mana twitching,  Chanters =  Mezz/charm/buffs ,  blah blah blah.<br>
<br>
Basically what I'm getting at is each class has it's own strengths and weaknesses.  One of our biggest strengths is CHARM and you wanna take that ability away from us?  Thats like Nerfing necros so they can't solo, or druids, or bards.  Hell any class that can solo.  Charm soloing is actually pretty risky when you think about it since we hold up to mobs beating on us about as good as butter stands up to a hot knife.  At lvl 58 I have just over 1700hp.  1700 divided by 250 comes out to roughly 7 hits and a nekkid chanter looking for a rezz.  Charm can save your butt on a raid or in an exp group.  It's one of our biggest assets and you want to nerf it, thats like nerfing Cheal for clerics man.  All because one of our strengths allows us to solo really well.  SO WHAT!  I'd like to be able to sow myself, I want to be able to heal myself, I want to be able to port to all druid/wiz location including hate and air, I'd also like to have the DD spells of a wiz and manaburn,  plus the killer dots of a necro and some better AC/hp buffs would be nice, maybe Virtue and symbol.  But just because &quot;I&quot; don't have them I'm not gonna advise VI to nerf the other classes so were &quot;balanced&quot;.<br>
<br>
