<br>
Consider me the &quot;minority&quot; then.  Just cause you chose to not try it doesn't make it balanced.<br>
<br>
If VI gave warriors unlimited instaclick CH's, and the warriors &quot;chose&quot; not to use the clicks, doesn't mean that the item is balanced.  There are maybe 4-6 chanters on my server that I see constantly camping 3rd tier pop mini's/zones with only CoD+hasted pets.  <br>
<br>
If your having a problem getting CoD to stick, then I truely feel sorry for you, it has a -100mr check (which means if mobs mr is 200, CoD only checks it as though it has 100mr), add tash beforehand and your basically unresistable and your charm should last for max 90% of the time (unless mob has &gt;250mr, or you weren't able to land tash, but I wouldn't charm what I can't tash).<br>
<br>
As far as the person who stated &quot;I didn't haste my pet, since on test they removed the ability to&quot;, this only makes sence if your on test.  Obviously, an unhasted pet isn't going to show you how grossly overpowered this is/was with hasted pets.<br>
<br>
I truely hope the changes on test go live, hasted CoD pets are overpowered, adding the slow to CoD thus removing the ability to haste brings it more inline with other classes, and more inline with risk-vs-reward.<br>
<br>
BTW, someone complaining about the cost of KeI spell, join a guild either they foot the bill (since it helps them) or make them go out and raid for it.  We have 8 copies of KeI in our bank, you wanna buy one, or would you rather join us and get a copy for free? Think about it.<br>
